Module io.github.mmm.nls
Package io.github.mmm.nls.argument

Interface NlsArguments

  • All Superinterfaces:
    NlsArgumentsKeys
    public interface NlsArguments
extends NlsArgumentsKeys
    A simple container for arguments used as dynamic arguments to fill into a NlsMessage. It is similar to Map but with less overhead in case there are only up to two arguments.
    See Also:
    NlsMessage.getArgument(String), NlsVariable

      • get

        Object get​(String key)
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the argument to get. Please prefer one of the KEY_* constants such as NlsArgumentsKeys.KEY_VALUE.
        Returns:
        the value of the argument with the given key or null if no such argument exists.
        See Also:
        Map.get(Object)

      • getKey

        String getKey​(int index)
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the requested key. Should be in the range from 0 to size-1.
        Returns:
        the requested key or null if the index is greater or equal to size.
